summary: This is an FBI 302 form documenting an interview with a witness/victim (referred to as 'O') conducted via video conference on July 26, 2021. The witness discusses her media consumption about the case, contact with other women involved, participation in the victim compensation fund, and preparations for the upcoming trial of Ghislaine Maxwell.

persons.name: Ghislaine Maxwell
persons.context: The subject of the investigation and upcoming trial. The witness discusses media coverage of Maxwell's arrest and her own past experiences related to Maxwell.

persons.name: Julie Brown
persons.context: A reporter from the Miami Herald with whom the witness was scheduled to interview but did not.

events.title: FBI Interview of Witness 'O'
events.description: An FBI interview conducted via video conference with a witness/victim in the Ghislaine Maxwell case. The witness discusses her knowledge, media interactions, and participation in the victim compensation fund.

events.title: Release of Documentaries and Podcast
events.description: The witness states she watched two 2020 documentaries and listened to a 2020 podcast about the case, as well as a Wondry podcast.

events.title: Witness Receives Victim Compensation
events.description: The witness participated in the victim compensation fund and received a lump sum payment of 1.5 million dollars.

locations: New York, New York, United States
keyFacts: A witness/victim ('O') was interviewed by the FBI on July 26, 2021, in preparation for the Ghislaine Maxwell trial.
The witness has been in contact with about 5 other women involved in the case, discussing their media experiences but not specific case details.
The witness received a $1.5 million lump sum payment from the victim compensation fund.
The witness had extensive media consumption about the case, including Netflix documentaries, podcasts, and New York Times articles.
A Court TV reporter contacted the witness after Ghislaine Maxwell's arrest, and the witness spoke with her.
